'''''Scott Adams Scoops''''' is a compilation of [[video games]] designed by [[Scott Adams (game designer)|Scott Adams]] and published by [[U.S. Gold]] for a variety of [[home computers]]: ''[[Pirate Adventure]]'', ''[[Strange Odyssey]]'', ''[[Voodoo Castle]]'', and ''Buckaroo Banzai''.

==Development==
The compilation features text–only versions of four games designed by [[Scott Adams (game designer)|Scott Adams]] and previously published by Adams' [[Adventure International]]: ''[[Pirate Adventure]]'' (1979), ''[[Strange Odyssey]]'' (1979), ''[[Voodoo Castle]]'' (1979), and ''Buckaroo Banzai'' (1985). ''Buckaroo Banzai'' (co-written with Philip Case) is based on the 1984 film ''[[The Adventures of Buckaroo Banzai Across the 8th Dimension]]'' and was previously only released for the [[TI-99/4A]].<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Compilation Corner|date=February 1987|magazine=[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]|page=11|issue=37|url=https://archive.org/stream/crash-magazine-37/Crash_37_Feb_1987#page/n9/mode/2up}}</ref><ref name="CVG"/>

